Air Products and Chemicals, Inc. (APD) Shares Bought by Sullivan Bruyette Speros & Blaney LLC


					Posted by Joanna Charbonneau on Jul 22nd, 2017 // No Comments




Sullivan Bruyette Speros & Blaney LLC raised its stake in shares of  Air Products and Chemicals, Inc. (NYSE:APD) by 0.4% during the first quarter, according to its most recent filing with the SEC. The fund owned 1,764 shares of the basic materials company’s stock after buying an additional 7 shares during the period. Sullivan Bruyette Speros & Blaney LLC’s holdings in Air Products and Chemicals were worth $239,000 at the end of the most recent quarter. 
Several other institutional investors have also added to or reduced their stakes in the stock. Renaissance Technologies LLC raised its stake in shares of  Air Products and Chemicals by 50.6% in the fourth quarter. Renaissance Technologies LLC now owns 571,800 shares of the basic materials company’s stock worth $82,236,000 after buying an additional 192,000 shares in the last quarter.  Sumitomo Mitsui Financial Group Inc. purchased a new stake in shares of  Air Products and Chemicals during the fourth quarter worth about $1,088,000.  Azimuth Capital Management LLC raised its stake in shares of  Air Products and Chemicals by 2.7% in the fourth quarter. Azimuth Capital Management LLC now owns 14,508 shares of the basic materials company’s stock worth $2,087,000 after buying an additional 383 shares in the last quarter.  Pacad Investment Ltd. purchased a new stake in shares of  Air Products and Chemicals during the fourth quarter worth about $1,103,000.  Finally, Glenhill Advisors LLC raised its stake in shares of  Air Products and Chemicals by 159.3% in the fourth quarter. Glenhill Advisors LLC now owns 698,736 shares of the basic materials company’s stock worth $100,492,000 after buying an additional 429,272 shares in the last quarter. Institutional investors and hedge funds own  89.20% of the company’s stock. 


 Get Air Products and Chemicals Inc. alerts:



Shares of Air Products and Chemicals, Inc. (NYSE APD) traded down 0.25% during trading on Friday, reaching $145.64. The company’s stock had a trading volume of 1,226,559 shares. Air Products and Chemicals, Inc. has a 12-month low of $129.00 and a 12-month high of $150.45. The stock has a market cap of $31.71 billion, a P/E ratio of 10.07 and a beta of 1.26. The stock’s 50-day moving average is $144.53 and its 200-day moving average is $141.82. 





Air Products and Chemicals (NYSE:APD) last released its quarterly earnings data on Thursday, April 27th. The basic materials company reported $1.43 EPS for the quarter, topping the Thomson Reuters’ consensus estimate of $1.38 by $0.05. The firm had revenue of $1.98 billion for the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $1.84 billion. Air Products and Chemicals had a return on equity of 19.26% and a net margin of 36.19%. The company’s quarterly revenue was up 11.4% on a year-over-year basis. During the same quarter in the previous year, the business earned $1.82 earnings per share.  Equities research analysts anticipate that  Air Products and Chemicals, Inc. will post $6.16 earnings per share for the current fiscal year. 
The firm also recently declared a quarterly dividend, which will be paid on Monday, November 13th. Investors of record on Tuesday, October 10th will be issued a dividend of $0.95 per share. The ex-dividend date of this dividend is Friday, October 6th. This represents a $3.80 dividend on an annualized basis and a yield of 2.61%. Air Products and Chemicals’s dividend payout ratio  is presently 26.28%. 
